In a LATEX document, we can generate a table of contents automatically by using the following commands:

1. Include the package for generating a table of contents:
```latex
\usepackage{tocbibind}
```

2. Use the following command to generate the table of contents:
```latex
\tableofcontents
```

3. Use section, subsection, and subsubsection commands to create the structure of the document, for example:
```latex
\section{Introduction}
\subsection{Background}
\subsubsection{Research Question}
\section{Literature Review}
```

Here's a complete example of a LATEX document with an automatically generated table of contents:
```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{tocbibind}

\begin{document}

\tableofcontents

\section{Introduction}
This is the introduction section.

\subsection{Background}
This is the background subsection.

\subsubsection{Research Question}
This is the research question subsubsection.

\section{Literature Review}
This is the literature review section.

\end{document}
```

